import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Values')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['values'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the volcano dataset?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['width'], data['height'])
    plt.title("Is there a correlation between the width and height of the volcano?")
    plt.xlabel("Width")
    plt.ylabel("Height")
    plt.legend(["Volcano"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['values'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average value of the volcano?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Values')
    ax.axhline(data['values'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['values'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['values'])
    ax.set_title('What is the range of values in the volcano dataset?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Values')
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Values'])
    min_value = data['values'].min()
    max_value = data['values'].max()
    ax.axhline(min_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Min: {min_value:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(max_value, color='g', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_value:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
